parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS pump can cause the anti-lock brake system to become inoperable, leading to reduced braking performance and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake warning indicator illuminates
the ABS system becomes inoperable
the motorcycle experiences reduced braking performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the final drive can cause the motorcycle to lose power and become difficult to control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Failure of the U-joints
drive shaft
final drive bearings
and gears
leading to loss of power and reduced control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked fuel pump mounting boss can cause fuel to leak onto the engine and exhaust system, potentially leading to a fire, especially when the engine and exhaust reach normal operating temperatures.
symptoms: Fuel sprays onto the back of the engine
fuel flows onto the exhaust system
smoke coming from under the vehicle when stopped
fuel running down the side of the engine onto the exhaust.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system failures can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, especially when the engine and exhaust reach normal operating temperatures.
symptoms: Fuel leaks
fuel sprays onto the engine
fuel flows onto the exhaust system
smoke coming from under the vehicle
fuel running down the side of the engine onto the exhaust.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent stalling of the engine can cause loss of control, especially when decelerating or braking, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine stalls repeatedly
often when decelerating to a stop
the motorcycle restarts immediately
but the stalling creates braking and traffic flow problems.
